# Jekyll Academic Website Structure

This is a Jekyll-powered academic personal website with the following key structure:

## Core Configuration
- Main config: [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) - Contains site settings, personal info, and social media links
- Local development: Run `bundle exec jekyll serve --trace` for local testing
- GitHub Pages deployment via GitHub Actions in [.github/workflows/cache_control.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/cache_control.yml)

## Content Structure
- **Main page**: [index.html](mdc:index.html) - Single-page layout with sections for About, Publications, Teaching, Projects, and Miscellaneous
- **Data files** in `_data/` directory:
  - [publications.yml](mdc:_data/publications.yml) - Academic publications
  - [projects.yml](mdc:_data/projects.yml) - Personal and academic projects  
  - [authors.yml](mdc:_data/authors.yml) - Collaborator information
  - [misc.yaml](mdc:_data/misc.yaml) - Awards, certificates, achievements
  - [hobbies.yml](mdc:_data/hobbies.yml) - Personal interests section
  - [navigation.yml](mdc:_data/navigation.yml) - Navigation menu items

## Styling & Assets
- **CSS Framework**: Bulma CSS framework ([bulma.min.css](mdc:css/bulma.min.css))
- **Custom styles**: [css/index.scss](mdc:css/index.scss) with SCSS imports from [_sass/_base.scss](mdc:_sass/_base.scss)
- **JavaScript**: [js/index.js](mdc:js/index.js) - Handles navbar, mouseover effects, and external links
- **Images**: Stored in `images/` with publication-specific subdirectories
- **Files**: PDFs and documents in `files/` directory

## Key Features
- Responsive design with mobile navbar burger menu
- Publication mouseover effects (image/video transitions)
- External links open in new tabs automatically
- Academic icons via Academicons and Font Awesome
- Google Fonts integration (Google Sans, Noto Sans)

## Content Management
- All personal information is centralized in [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml)
- Publications, projects, and other content managed via YAML data files
- Images should be 1:1 aspect ratio, minimum 320px as noted in [README.md](mdc:README.md)
- Shared template [_includes/section.html](mdc:_includes/section.html) for consistent content rendering
